<h1 class="hero-h">Real estate AI playbook <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for brokerages and property companies.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Real estate AI in 2026 has matured past the AI staging novelty. The brokerages and property management companies seeing real returns are using AI on the boring high-volume work — listing copy, market reports, tenant communications, deal docs. This is that playbook.</p>
</div></div>

<div style="background:#0A1A0A;border-top:1px solid #1A3A1A;border-bottom:1px solid #1A3A1A;padding:1.25rem 2.5rem;">
<div style="max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:0.78rem;color:#8FAF8F;">
<div>By <a href="/about" style="color:#F0FFF0;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Bill Colbert</a> · <span style="color:#4A6A4A;">Founder, Treetop Growth Strategy</span></div>
<div style="color:#4A6A4A;">Published May 2026 · <a href="/content-library" style="color:#8FAF8F;text-decoration:none;">More from the library</a></div>
</div>
</div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Where the wins are</span><h2 class="h2">Five workflows</h2><h3 class="h3">1. Listing descriptions &amp; marketing copy</h3><p class="body">Generate listing descriptions, social posts, email blasts from property details in minutes. Agent time recovered for high-value selling activities.</p><h3 class="h3">2. Buyer/seller communications</h3><p class="body">Drafts of update emails, status notes, offer follow-ups. Agent reviews and sends. Higher touchpoint frequency without higher time cost.</p><h3 class="h3">3. Market reports for clients</h3><p class="body">Personalized quarterly or monthly market reports for past clients (top source of repeat &amp; referral business). Move from "never produced" to "every quarter" with AI.</p><h3 class="h3">4. Transaction documentation summaries</h3><p class="body">Summarize inspection reports, title docs, disclosure packages into client-friendly summaries. Faster client decisions.</p><h3 class="h3">5. Tenant communications (property management)</h3><p class="body">Maintenance request triage, routine tenant communications, lease renewal outreach. Massive volume work where AI assistance scales the property manager.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Where to be cautious</span><h2 class="h2">Workflows to defer or skip</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Pricing recommendations.</strong> Use comparative market analysis tools, not LLMs. Pricing is too high-stakes for AI-only judgment.</li><li><strong>Contract drafting from scratch.</strong> Use your forms; let AI fill them or summarize them. Do not let AI improvise legal documents.</li><li><strong>AI-generated property photos beyond staging.</strong> Disclosure requirements vary by jurisdiction; honesty risks outpace photo aesthetics.</li><li><strong>Auto-replies to tenant emergencies.</strong> Routing is fine; substantive responses to safety/maintenance urgent issues should be human.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Brokerage rollout</span><h2 class="h2">Adoption patterns</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Top-producing agents first.</strong> Their adoption signals everyone else.</li><li><strong>Workflow-specific training.</strong> Generic AI demos do not convert agents. "Here is how you get a listing description in 90 seconds" does.</li><li><strong>Shared prompt library.</strong> Agents copy what works from each other faster than they invent new workflows.</li><li><strong>Brokerage-level enterprise seats.</strong> Do not make agents pay for personal accounts. Provision properly.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Property management rollout</span><h2 class="h2">Different shape</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Property manager + admin team train together.</strong> The workflow split matters; both need the same vocabulary.</li><li><strong>Integration with property management software.</strong> The bigger ROI comes from AI summarizing and drafting around existing systems, not replacing them.</li><li><strong>Tenant-facing communications need brand voice.</strong> Build a Project with brand voice guide and example correspondence.</li><li><strong>Vendor communications.</strong> AI drafts for contractor scheduling and follow-up are an underrated workflow.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Budget</span><h2 class="h2">Typical numbers</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Small brokerage (5-15 agents):</strong> \$5K-\$20K Year 1 including platform + light implementation.</li><li><strong>Mid-sized brokerage (15-50 agents):</strong> \$15K-\$60K Year 1.</li><li><strong>Property management company (\$5M-\$25M revenue):</strong> \$10K-\$50K Year 1.</li></ul></div></section>

